&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercise&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Enable out-of-the-box metrics&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;section class="step"&gt;
&lt;div class="step__num"&gt;1&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;header class="step__head"&gt;&lt;p class="step__title"&gt;Open your log stream settings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="step__body"&gt;&lt;!-- PLACEHOLDER UI NAVIGATION: replace with exact console steps + screenshot once finalized --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the Galileo console (&lt;code&gt;https://console.multitenant.galileocloud.io&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;workshop&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; org),
open your project and select the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;default&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; log stream.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Review Metric Scores</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/ai/4-splunk-agent-observability/6-enable-metrics/2-review-metric-scores/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/ai/4-splunk-agent-observability/6-enable-metrics/2-review-metric-scores/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;After a few moments, we&amp;rsquo;ll see how the existing traces get automatically scored on the
&lt;code&gt;Context Adherence&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;Correctness&lt;/code&gt; metrics.
This is where a hallucinated dosage or a wrong tool call stops being invisible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
